00:00:57.208 --> 00:00:59.809
testosterone creams ...

00:00:59.833 --> 00:01:03.208
even untested genital injections.

00:01:04.625 --> 00:01:09.042
The thing is, female sexuality
can't be fixed with a pill.

00:01:09.958 --> 00:01:12.309
That's because it's not broken:

00:01:12.333 --> 00:01:14.042
it's misunderstood.

00:01:14.667 --> 00:01:19.143
Our culture has had a skewed
and medically incorrect picture

00:01:19.167 --> 00:01:21.143
of female sexuality

00:01:21.167 --> 00:01:23.684
going back centuries.

00:01:23.708 --> 00:01:28.434
If over half of women
have some kind of sexual problem,

00:01:28.458 --> 00:01:32.292
maybe our idea of sexuality
doesn't work for women.

00:01:33.083 --> 00:01:37.083
We need a clearer understanding
of how women actually work.

00:01:38.917 --> 00:01:40.184
I'm a journalist,

00:01:40.208 --> 00:01:41.643
and I recently wrote a book

00:01:41.667 --> 00:01:46.000
about how our understanding
of female sexuality is evolving.

00:01:46.750 --> 00:01:52.250
So sexuality itself was defined
back when men dominated science.

00:01:53.208 --> 00:01:55.434
Male scientists
